items.headline: England beat Pakistan - video & text
items.summary: In-play video highlights and reaction as Joe Root hits 89 to set up England's four-wicket win over Pakistan in the second ODI at Lord's.

items.headline: England beat Pakistan to take 2-0 lead

90948938.altText: Mark Wood (centre) is congratulated by England team-mates

items.summary: England produce another polished display to beat Pakistan at Lord's by four wickets and take a 2-0 lead in the one-day series.

items.headline: Stunning Plunkett catch removes Wahab
items.summary: England's Liam Plunkett takes a stunning catch at extra-cover to remove Wahab Riaz and reduce Pakistan to 236-8 in the second one-day international at Lord's.

items.headline: Root collides with Rashid as he catches Hasan

37205301.caption: Root collides with Rashid as he catches Hasan

items.summary: England's Joe Root collides with team-mate Adil Rashid as he catches Hasan Ali in Pakistan's innings of 251.

items.headline: Anderson & Broad to miss rest of season
items.overtypedHeadline: Anderson & Broad to miss rest of domestic season
items.summary: James Anderson and Stuart Broad will miss the rest of the domestic season as they recover from injuries before the winter Tests.

items.headline: West Indies hit record 21 sixes in T20
items.summary: Evin Lewis, playing his second game, smashes a 48-ball century as West Indies amass the third highest T20 international total in history.

items.headline: Bangladesh upbeat over England security

90947541.caption: Bangladesh Cricket Board president Nazmul Hasan Papon
90947541.altText: Bangladesh Cricket Board president Nazmul Hasan Papon

items.summary: The head of the Bangladesh Cricket Board says he is confident there "won't be any problem" with security when England tour there this autumn.

items.headline: Yorkshire beat Notts to boost title bid
items.summary: Yorkshire close to within five points of Division One leaders Middlesex by wrapping up a 305-run win over Nottinghamshire.

items.headline: Worcs chase 401 to beat Northants
items.summary: Daryl Mitchell and Joe Clarke score centuries as Worcestershire chase 401 to beat Northants by two wickets.

items.headline: Sussex edge thriller with Glamorgan
items.summary: Sussex remain unbeaten in Division Two as they edge to a dramatic two-wicket triumph over Glamorgan in Cardiff.

items.headline: Footitt best sets up easy Surrey win
items.summary: Mark Footitt claims a career-best 7-62 before Surrey reach a modest target of 38 to beat Lancashire by 10 wickets.
